title: Aoshima
author: Unknown
pages:
Aoshima (often
referred to as "Cat
Island") is a small
island in Ehime
Prefecture famous
for its large
population of cats.
Cats on Aoshima used
to outnumber humans
by around 6 to 1, but
as the human
population declined
there are now 36 cats
for every human.

Editor's Note:

These cats are
literally just wool
blocks, levers, and
signs, but they are so
fricking cute, man._
